children.subject: 189 uses maximum likelihood estimators, which is taught in 135. Definitely is somewhat useful
OP here. They're also taught in 140, is there any other overlap with 135 or should I just switch to DS100?
just take 127 in place of 135. I'm in 135 right now and I'm not sure how much of it is actually useful... The labs do take up quite some amount of time so I think you should go for 127 instead.

DS gives a more gentle intro to lots of relevant material in 189. I’m taking them concurrently right now and put 0 explicit effort into Data 100 to understand the concepts, as studying for CS189 gets me where I need for Data 100 and then some.

history.content: In Stat 135 right now, and most of the things you learn in 135 doesn't seem all that applicable to 189. I'd take 100 over 135 if it were between the 2.

As title. I plan to take 61C in the fall and 189 in the spring, and so don't think I'd be able to add EE 127 for the fall due to the workload of 61C + another tech elective. Should I consider another course like DS100 as better preparation for 189? My knowledge of linear algebra is EE16AB level and I've taken multivariable calculus and Stat 140(I didn't feel my aptitude for probability was strong enough after taking 70, otherwise I'd have taken 126).
